review_blob: The top blow off with a bang. Its a good thing it was well settle in the refrigerate or it would have gushed. I am new to this style but so far this is my favorite

Hazy a light yellow, nice head . Pleasant aroma , sour ... more than expected, dry, yeasty, the oak adds to the dryness very noticeable. Not liking it at first, but its growing on me fast. Ok I enjoyed it . Alcohol is not part of the flavor.

Coal tar Black beer with a creamy brown head. Burnt grain aroma, coffee, caramel citrus. Flavor is tart, bitter chocolate, a bit of bitter for the sake of bitter and molasses but it could be burnt as well. Not one of my top stouts
beer_name: Hales Pikop Andropovs Rushin Imperial Stout

review_blob: Lively head large bubbles moving fast. Light fruity aroma, flavor is very refreshing a little sweet and fruity but also a bit tart. Alcohol is completely hidden 9% and I would honestly drink this on a hot day when thirsty

Lively head large bubbles moving fast. Light fruity aroma, flavor is very refreshing a little sweet and fruity but also a bit tart. Alcohol is completely hidden 9% and I would honestly drink this on a hot day when thirsty

Dark amber, light small bubbled head. Malty nose with a floral note. Malty flavor just a little toasted flavor and a subdued hop bitterness. But still more hops than is typical for the style. Overall a good example of an American version of a Scotch ale
beer_name: Boundary Bay Scotch Ale - Highland Reserve

review_blob:
The sign at Bottleworks said that this beer was probably better than what you were thinking of buying

Happier than one would think for the style but then this is Victory. Fruity, a bit spicy a easy drinking beer. I cant seem to give this beer a proper deScription lets just say the boys of Bottleworks were right
Dark mahogany in color. Tan, small, creamy and long lasting head. Sweet aroma, Grapes? Sweet, bitter flavor, medium bodied, sticky sweet at the end with a bitter finish.
UPDATED: APR 21, 2004
UPDATED: APR 11, 2004
UPDATED: APR 24, 2004

Dirty yellow with a very lively and large head that behaves much like Champaign. Speaking of champagne this beer has a hint of that smell in it. Tart dry flavor, alcohol is a big part of this beers flavor, no subtlety about it. The slightest hint of fruit with a little sweetness at the end. Not an exciting beer but enjoyable
Dark brown, tan head, smooth, sweet, malty, dried fruit, alcohol and a bit of coffee at the end. Nice warming finish

Ok so I see this stuff at a dollar store in a small town $3.40 a six pack. What the hell its cheep. Dark reddish brown, thick tan head. Sweet hoppy aroma, a hint of coffee. Medium bodied sweet flavor a little grainy and a bit of fruit, hop bitterness cleans it all up in the end. Im buying more
Light brown, light nice thick head, hoppy floral aroma. Sweet, light to medium boded, mildly bitter ends a bit bitter. Very drinkable one of the more balanced American IPAs

Dark brown, nice tight bubbled head that hung on the until the end. Malty, nutty aroma. Flavor toasted malt molasses sweet caramel flavor neutral hop bitterness that tends to dry it up a bit. They say its peated but the peat is so subdued I cant place it. Clean alcohol profile, barely noticeable perfectly balanced scotch ale authentic and very good. A winner and lets not forget the cool bottle
Dark brown a little on the red side, medium sized creamy head that diminishes rather quickly but never goes completely down. Mildly sweet lightly toasty hops take over and dry it out in the end.

Ok this beer is on the brown side of yellow with a nice small bubbled white head. The aroma is typical northwest IPA, a bit floral and citrusy. But aroma of malt is there. Alcohol is very well hidden and comes across as more a sweet flavor rather than harsh a pine citrus flavor comes through but its not over powering.
beer_name: Silver City Whoop Pass Double IPA

review_blob: They might saved this beer for summer but for an ale brewery this is a great Pilsener. Yellow not completely clear but medium bubbled hear. Classic Czech hop aroma but they say they didnt use Czech hops. They fooled me. Lacking a little in the malt part of this brew but not bad.

Yep looks just like a porter, almost black but you can still see through it, thick head. Hop aroma (citrusy) makes it through the coffeeish roasted smell. Complex flavor lots of roasted flavors a bit dry for style but I like it a lot more than my rating may tell you. This is a very drinkable beer

Clear amber medium bubbled almost white head. Mild sweet aroma a combination of hops and grain giving this a different aroma but maybe I just getting to comfortable with hop monsters. A hop monster this beer is not. Medium light bodied beer smooth drinking a definite grainy flavor but not an unpleasant one. A floral hop flavor comes though a balanced beer and a great session beer
Dark amber big tan head that holds up well nice complex hop aroma toasty malt flavor hop bitterness takes over. A good beer but Rogue has so many better

Brown, sort of an orange head what little there is of it. Sweet big fruity aroma, a great aroma. Wonderful what happens to a big old beer like this after a few years of aging. Dried fruits a bit of wine hop bitterness has lived on and balances this beers big malt flavor out. The after taste stays with you and makes you cry for more but there is so little of this beer left in the world.

Big champagne like head, light orange in color a little hazy. What a pleasant aroma definitely a Belgian yeast and a good amount of wheat in this beer. Bananas can be smelled a bit of unidentified spice in the aroma yeah there is an orange smell as well. The flavor matches the aroma, mildly sweet light to medium bodied. A great beer to the best of my knowledge there are only 3 bottles left in Washington State. Help us Casta

Clear dark amber tan head. Aroma, fruity citrus notes standing out. First the typical grapefruit hop flavor hits but is mellowed out by a very nice rich and somewhat sweet malt base the toasted flavors are here. By Stone standards this beer is almost balanced
UPDATED: APR 2, 2004
Clear dark brown big light head. Medium bodied a bit fruity and earthy, a very light but pleasant malt flavor. This is a real winner

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Bang! That was the second hair of the dog beer I have had go off like a bomb. But shockingly after the big bang it was not over carbonated but the head is big, fine bubbled and never goes away. A huge aroma, sweet malt, apricots and citrus. Medium full boded a little sticky the alcohol seems to thin out the perception of fullness. Figs, raisins, molasses, caramel balanced nicely with a pleasant hop bit. Leave you wanting another. A different barley wine but I would call it that over anything else.
beer_name: Hair of the Dog Doggie Claws (2001-2002)

review_blob: Big tan head, dark brown. Complex aroma, a little of everything, roasted malts, citrus alcohol. Big hops but balanced with a bigger dark malt flavore. Not a sweet beer but a big, big beer.

Dark brown orange medium head. Strong pleasant spicy sweet aroma with a citrus. Rich bodied alcohol very noticeable, sweet, a little fruity, noticeable hop bitterness. Flavors need to mellow but a very good beer.

Ok whats wrong here. The light hop bitterness is to much considering the lack of anything besides  a light sour flavor to balence this beer out. Light, sour, bitter and dry. Yuk! LaConner is a great brewery but stay away from this one
The hop bitterness is a little much but it grows on you as you keep drinking. Alcohol adds a little to the flavor profile. More head, more hop, more malt. Its good
beer_name: Diamond Knot Industrial India Pale Ale

review_blob: Aroma yeah! Big sweet grapefruit aroma. Cloudy, orange in color, small medium bubbled but ever lasting head good lacing. Big hop flavor but far from over done there is malt here. Really this is just a prefect northwestern style IPA. A special beer or a session beer its ether one. One of the very best

Dark brown a little cloudy, abundant large bubbled head. Citrus aroma and light toast, malt. Medium boded rich flavor, malt roasted and otherwise, citrus, pine a pleasant bitter finish. A great tribute to a dog

beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: This beer is subtle, light color, little head, clear. Very mild aroma but a complex one, sweet, malty, flowers and wine but again the aroma is subtle. Alcohol? You just cant taste it but at 10% its there when you stand up.  Favor is mildly malty, floral, spices but all so very subtle and blended. A fabulous beer but if your taste buds are blown out by drunkenness or you just drank a hopmoster this beer is not for you, your not worthy

Dark red brown, creamy head what little there was. Complex aroma molasses roasted grains, wine. This is a real big beer once it hits your mouth caramel raisins wine chocolate but smooth and drinkable. Pleasant aftertaste. Another great Fish Tale seasonal

Fruity hop aroma, brown, a bit cloudy. The head had a very short life. Medium bodied, sticks a bit to your lips, a little sweet, hop bitterness balances this out . The beer leans a little bit on the hoppy side but this is not an imperial IPA. A very good American strong ale I will never know if it would age well It didnt last long in this house
Clear yellow, good sized head ,median bead. Sweet hoppy aroma. Mildly sweet, strong hop flavor medium boded beer . A great Pilsener

Looks like a shot of express, very mild aroma of roasted malts. Light bodied for imperial stout, alcohol is well hidden ,smooth, well crafted beer. No yeast flavors almost lager like its so clean flavored.

Dark amber with a long lasting white head. A nice aroma of malt and hops. The flavor is hoppy. The malt and toasted malts balances this thing out. Im impressed a great beer that isnt an ultra big beer, just a good session beer. No make that a great session beer. Now if they would just ship a keg of this to Enumclaw Wa.
Good looking beer dark, reddish amber nice head. Spicy complex aromas I cant seems to put a name to all the smells here.  Slightly sweet tart and fruity. Not bad at all
Cute little head but it died so young. Amber in color, very mild malty aroma and a very mild malty flavor.  A good easy drinking mild beer. Its winner but nothing special
No point waxing poetic about this one.  Well made, flawless, drinkable, enjoyable, a bit malty. Dull and spiceless

Carbonated yes it is, golden color with a moderate head. Has that Champaign feeling in the mouth that is not all that unusual in a Belgian beer. Its a bit light I would say at the risk of being excommunicate by the beer gods that this Belgian uses too much sugar. A bit cidery, nice hop profile lightly bitter a very refreshing beer.

My brother in law felt bad about the first beer he picked up [Eureka] for me so he ran out and got this stuff. Ok this isnt bad. Out of whack as all IPAs are, a bit thin and one dimensional in its hop profile. An average IPA buy it if its on sale
UPDATED: MAR 27, 2004

Eureka my bother in law knew I like a good micro brew so he bought me some Eureka Pale Ale. Thanks that was the worst supposed micro beer I have ever had. Headless, rich yellow in color, over carbonated. They say its all malt and that must be true how else could such a strong husk flavor come through. But enjoy that tannic flavor as that is about all the flavor this thing has at all. I would just as soon drink Miller at lest it can be drank near frozen were you cant taste it.

For a northwest IPA the hops are not that intense but if youre not a hop fan this one may not be for you.  A good introductionion into the ultra hoppy northwestern IPS. Light to medium bodied, nice but mellow citrus aroma.  My glass was very clear, light amber, lightly carbonated with a small persistent head. Clean finish
UPDATED: SEP 1, 2003
UPDATED: APR 13, 2004
